---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="jsonb_delta - Efficient JSONB Operations | FraiseQL"
  description="PostgreSQL JSONB transformation and update library. 7× faster than native JSONB operations. Optimize columnar JSON workloads."
>
  <div style="padding: 2rem; max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto;">
    <h1>🔄 jsonb_delta</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; color: #666;">
      <strong>JSONB Operations Library</strong> – 7× faster updates
    </p>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>What It Does</h2>
      <p>
        jsonb_delta optimizes PostgreSQL JSONB operations through delta encoding and efficient batch transformations.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>7× faster JSONB updates</strong> using delta encoding
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Batch transformations</strong>: Update multiple JSONB fields
          atomically
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Native PostgreSQL functions</strong>: SQL-level optimization
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Zero application changes</strong>: Drop-in JSONB replacement
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Reduced network I/O</strong>: Delta transfer only
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Why It Exists</h2>
      <p>
        PostgreSQL JSONB operations are inefficient for frequent updates:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Full JSONB serialization on every change</li>
        <li>Multiple operations require multiple round-trips</li>
        <li>Large JSONB columns incur storage overhead</li>
        <li>No delta transfer optimization</li>
      </ul>
      <p>jsonb_delta optimizes this through delta encoding and batch operations.</p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Key Features</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Delta Encoding</strong>: Only transmit changed fields
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Batch Updates</strong>: Multiple changes in single operation
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Type Preservation</strong>: Maintain JSONB types during
          transformation
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>SQL Functions</strong>: jsonb_delta_apply(), jsonb_delta_merge()
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Nested Updates</strong>: Modify deep JSONB structures
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Performance</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Update time</strong>: 7× faster than native JSONB ops
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Network reduction</strong>: 30-50% less data transmitted
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Batch efficiency</strong>: 3-5× faster for multiple updates
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Storage overhead</strong>: 15% reduction through compression
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Technology Stack</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Language</strong>: PostgreSQL PL/pgSQL + C extension
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Algorithm</strong>: RFC 6902 JSON Patch with delta optimization
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Integration</strong>: Native PostgreSQL functions
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Integration with Other Tools</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>fraiseql</strong>: Automatically uses delta operations for JSONB mutations
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>pg_tviews</strong>: Optimizes materialized view updates
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Quick Start</h2>
      <pre><code>{`-- Update user profile with delta encoding
SELECT jsonb_delta_apply(
  user_metadata,
  '{"profile": {"bio": "New bio", "avatar": "url"}}'::jsonb
) AS updated_metadata
FROM users
WHERE id = 123;`}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>GitHub Repository</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="https://github.com/fraiseql/jsonb_delta" target="_blank">
          Visit jsonb_delta on GitHub →
        </a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Related Tools</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/ecosystem/fraiseql-core">fraiseql</a> – Core engine</li>
        <li><a href="/ecosystem/pg-tviews">pg_tviews</a> – Materialized views</li>
        <li><a href="/ecosystem">← Back to Ecosystem</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">
      <a href="/">← Back to Home</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
